The paper presents a framework for object instance segmentation, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves deep learning and neural networks, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method also involves object detection and recognition, which are topics in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper presents results on the COCO dataset, which is a benchmark for multimedia analysis (cs.MM).
